<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="CC3" checkit-title="Constant-Coefficient Linear Homogeneous Higher-Order ODEs">
  <statement>
    <p>Explain how to find the general solution to each given ODE using
        exponential functions.</p>
    <p>For each exponential solution using complex numbers, also provide
        an alternate general solution using only real numbers.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
            <me>300 \, {y} + 3 \, {y''} = -60 \, {y'}</me>
        </li>
        <li>
            <me>2 \, {y''} = -68 \, {y} - 20 \, {y'}</me>
        </li>
        <li>
            <me>-3 \, {y'''} - 24 \, {y'} = 18 \, {y''}</me>
        </li>
      </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <ol>
        <li><me>
            
            {y} = k_{1} t e^{\left(-10 \, t\right)} + k_{2} e^{\left(-10 \, t\right)}
         </me></li>
        <li><me>
            {y} = c_{1} e^{\left(3 \, i t - 5 \, t\right)} + c_{2} e^{\left(-3 \, i t - 5 \, t\right)};\qquad
            {y} = {\left(k_{1} \cos\left(3 \, t\right) + k_{2} \sin\left(3 \, t\right)\right)} e^{\left(-5 \, t\right)}
         </me></li>
        <li><me>
            
            {y} = k_{2} e^{\left(-2 \, t\right)} + k_{1} e^{\left(-4 \, t\right)} + k_{3}
         </me></li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
